## Introduction

I find that one of the biggest annoyances with SharePoint Online and Modern Pages is the lack of customisation options you have available.

For example, if you want to make a clickable tile with a different look and feel then your options are limited.

### Create List

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Click on the **Cog** in the top left corner of the screen and then select **Site contents**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Click on new and select **List**.

Create a blank list

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Give it a name, I have called mine _Web Applications_ and click **create.**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Click on **Edit in grid view**

Add the following column by clicking + Add Column

Hyperlink

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Type name as **URL** and click **save**

### Add another column

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Type name as **ImageUrl** and click **save**

You now should have a SharePoint list that looks like this.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Type into Title the name of the application >> Excel  
Type into URL the default link to Excel online >> [https://www.office.com/launch/excel?auth=2](https://www.office.com/launch/excel?auth=2 "https://www.office.com/launch/excel?auth=2") and give it the name of Excel for Web  
Type into the ImageUrl the link to the Excel icon >> [https://spoppe-b.azureedge.net/files/fabric-cdn-prod_20211104.001/assets/item-types/32/xlsx.svg](https://spoppe-b.azureedge.net/files/fabric-cdn-prod_20211104.001/assets/item-types/32/xlsx.svg "https://spoppe-b.azureedge.net/files/fabric-cdn-prod_20211104.001/assets/item-types/32/xlsx.svg")

You should now have this

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Now we will add the formatting. Click on **All Items** and select **Format current view**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

From **Choose Layout** select Gallery and then select **advanced mode**

Copy and Paste in the Code from the code block below and click **save**

### Code

{{< highlight json >}}

{ "$schema": "[https://developer.microsoft.com/json-schemas/sp/v2/tile-formatting.schema.json](https://developer.microsoft.com/json-schemas/sp/v2/tile-formatting.schema.json "https://developer.microsoft.com/json-schemas/sp/v2/tile-formatting.schema.json")", "hideSelection": true, "width": "202", "height": "194", "formatter": { "elmType": "a", "attributes": { "href": "\[$URL\]", "target": "'_blank')" }, "style": { "text-decoration": "none" }, "children": \[ { "elmType": "div", "attributes": { "class": "ms-bgColor-neutralLight ms-bgColor-neutralLighter--hover ms-fontColor-neutralDark ms-fontColor-neutralDark--hover" }, "style": { "display": "flex", "flex-wrap": "wrap", "min-width": "200px", "min-height": "180px", "margin-right": "10px", "margin-top": "10px", "box-shadow": "2px 2px 4px darkgrey" }, "children": \[ { "elmType": "div", "style": { "text-align": "center", "margin": "auto" }, "children": \[ { "elmType": "div", "attributes": { "class": "sp-row-title" }, "style": { "font-weight": "400", "font-size": "1.2em", "padding-bottom": "0.6em" }, "txtContent": "\[$Title\]" }, { "elmType": "img", "style": { "width": "50%" }, "attributes": { "src": "\[$ImageUrl\]" } } \] } \] } \] } }

{{< /highlight >}}

You should now see a link for excel.

In same way you can add the links for word, powerpoint, teams and outlook.
